# SysDope authoring rules

- **Never invent scientific data.** Every scientific claim shown in the UI
  must be backed by a `Citation` object pointing to a real source (PubChem,
  Rhea, UniProt, ChEBI, HMDB, USDA FoodData Central, peer-reviewed paper,
  etc.). When unsure, use a `confidence: "low"` placeholder citation that
  links to the relevant database landing page rather than fabricating data.
- The simulation engine in `lib/simulation` is **headless and pure TypeScript**
  with no React imports. UI animation state must live in components, not in
  the simulation store.
- Concentrations must clamp to `>= 0` after every tick.
- Default simulation values are educational placeholders unless explicitly
  source-backed in seed data.
- All UI numeric levels must be labeled "relative simulation units" — never
  "ng/mL", "mol/L", or any clinical unit unless source-backed.
- The global disclaimer "Educational simulation only. Not medical advice."
  must remain visible on every page.
